<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<pretext>
  <article xml:id="task3-spectral-localizer-edge">
    <title>Task 3: Localizer Heatmap and Edge States</title>
    <section xml:id="task3-overview">
      <title>Overview</title>
      <p>
        This note accompanies the two-dimensional spectral-localizer heatmap. Each lattice point
        is assigned the smallest singular scale of the localizer
        <m>
          L_{(x,y,\lambda)} =
          \kappa (X-xI)\otimes \Gamma_1 +
          \kappa (Y-yI)\otimes \Gamma_2 +
          (H-\lambda I)\otimes \Gamma_3.
        </m>
      </p>
      <p>
        Regions where the localizer gap becomes small indicate where the finite system is close
        to local topological activity or edge-state support.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section xml:id="task3-edge-density">
      <title>Edge Density Overlay</title>
      <p>
        The overlaid density map is formed from open-boundary eigenstates nearest the Fermi level.
        When the weight is concentrated on the outer sites, the overlay traces physical edge
        localization directly in real space, without Bloch decomposition.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</pretext>
